            "id": "ch02-rat-page-4",
            "slug": "rat-page-4",
            "title": "RAT: Reading Test — Page 4",
            "content": "## Apply Questions\r\n\r\n**17. A hospital administrator wants to know whether a new scheduling system reduced patient wait times. The administrator compares average wait times from the three months before and after the system launched. Which chapter concept does this most directly illustrate?**\r\n\r\nA. The DIKW hierarchy\r\n\r\nB. Using a KPI to measure performance improvement\r\n\r\nC. The five-component framework\r\n\r\nD. IT governance\r\n\r\n**18. Select ALL that apply: A coffee shop owner installs new point-of-sale software but does not train staff, update inventory processes, or define data entry standards. Six months later, reports are inconsistent and staff do not trust the numbers. Applying the chapter's concepts, which problems does this scenario illustrate?**\r\n\r\nA. Confusing IT (the software) with IS (the full system)\r\n\r\nB. Neglecting the people and processes components of the five-component framework\r\n\r\nC. A failure of data quality (inconsistent entries)\r\n\r\nD. A strategic alignment failure — the software does not fit the business\r\n\r\nE. The software is defective and must be replaced\r\n\r\n**19. A call center manager sets a KPI of \"average handling time under three minutes.\" Staff begin cutting calls short and leaving issues unresolved. Which chapter insight does this scenario illustrate?**\r\n\r\nA. KPIs are always harmful\r\n\r\nB. KPIs shape behavior, and poorly designed KPIs can encourage the wrong behavior\r\n\r\nC. Average handling time is an invalid metric\r\n\r\nD. Call centers should not use any KPIs\r\n\r\n**20. A university wants to build a system to identify students at risk of failing. Using the R.E.A.D. framework, which stage involves structuring grade records, attendance data, and assignment submissions so they can be queried?**\r\n\r\nA. Expression and Experience\r\n\r\nB. Association and Acquisition\r\n\r\nC. Representation and Retrieval\r\n\r\nD. Decision-Making and Deployment\r\n\r\n**21. Using the chapter's online retailer example, match the activity to the correct R.E.A.D. stage: \"A dashboard displays order volume, late shipments, and customer complaints.\"**\r\n\r\nA. Representation and Retrieval\r\n\r\nB. Expression and Experience\r\n\r\nC. Association and Acquisition\r\n\r\nD. Decision-Making and Deployment\r\n\r\n**22. Select ALL that apply: A well-designed KPI, according to the chapter, should have which of the following?**\r\n\r\nA. A clear business goal\r\n\r\nB. A precise formula\r\n\r\nC. A reliable data source\r\n\r\nD. A refresh cycle\r\n\r\nE. A colorful dashboard display\r\n\r\n**23. A retail chain discovers through analysis that late deliveries spike when one specific warehouse is understaffed. Applying the DIKW hierarchy, what level has the chain reached?**\r\n\r\nA. Data\r\n\r\nB. Information\r\n\r\nC. Knowledge\r\n\r\nD. Wisdom\r\n\r\n**24. A small business owner keeps all records in a single spreadsheet and manually emails reports to three managers every Monday. As the business grows to 50 employees, reports are often late and contain errors. Which chapter concept best explains why this approach is breaking down?**\r\n\r\nA. The DIKW hierarchy no longer applies to larger organizations\r\n\r\nB. Problems of scale, consistency, and coordination make formal information systems necessary\r\n\r\nC. Spreadsheets are never appropriate for business use\r\n\r\nD. The business needs more powerful hardware",
