            "content": "# Chapter 4: Introduction to Databases\r\n\r\nThis chapter introduces databases as structured systems that replace fragile file environments — covering DBMS architecture, relational tables, primary and foreign keys, constraints, and the bridge from spreadsheets to governed, multi-user data systems.\r\n\r\n## Chapter Files\r\n\r\n- [Main Chapter](core-concepts.md)\r\n- [Let's Build](lets-build.md)\r\n- [Review & Reflection](review-questions.md)\r\n- [Terms Treasury](terms-treasury.md)\r\n- [Readiness Assessment Test](rat.md)\r\n<!-- Lab not yet in publishing repo: [Lab 04: Intro to Access](lab-04-questions-2026-06-03.md) -->",
