            "slug": "rat-page-2",
            "title": "RAT: Reading Test — Page 2",
            "content": "## Remember Questions\r\n\r\n**1. What is a DBMS?**\r\n\r\nA. A collection of related data stored in tables\r\nB. The software engine that creates, manages, queries, secures, and administers databases\r\nC. A set of forms and reports that users interact with\r\nD. A programming language for building websites\r\n\r\n**2. Which sequence correctly describes the layers of a database system from top to bottom?**\r\n\r\nA. Database → DBMS → Applications → Users\r\nB. Users → Applications → DBMS → Database\r\nC. DBMS → Database → Users → Applications\r\nD. Applications → Users → Database → DBMS\r\n\r\n**3. What is a primary key?**\r\n\r\nA. A field that can be left empty for some records\r\nB. A field or combination of fields that uniquely identifies each row and cannot be NULL\r\nC. A column in one table that references a column in another table\r\nD. The first column in every table by convention\r\n\r\n**4. Select ALL that apply: Which are named constraint types in Chapter 4?**\r\n\r\nA. NOT NULL\r\nB. UNIQUE\r\nC. AUTO_SORT\r\nD. FOREIGN KEY\r\nE. CHECK\r\n\r\n**5. Which term describes the ability to change physical storage without changing the logical view users see?**\r\n\r\nA. Data redundancy\r\nB. Data independence\r\nC. Program-data dependence\r\nD. Concurrency control\r\n\r\n**6. Select ALL that apply: Which are valid reasons Chapter 4 gives for why databases matter to organizations?**\r\n\r\nA. They create a centralized source of truth\r\nB. They reduce data redundancy\r\nC. They eliminate the need for any human decision-making\r\nD. They improve accuracy through rules and constraints\r\nE. They enable shared governance of data\r\n\r\n**7. What is a foreign key?**\r\n\r\nA. A key that is imported from another database system\r\nB. A column in one table that references the primary key of another table\r\nC. The key that is used most frequently in queries\r\nD. A key that is automatically generated by the DBMS\r\n\r\n**8. Select ALL that apply: Which modification anomalies does Chapter 4 describe in flat tables?**\r\n\r\nA. Insertion anomaly\r\nB. Calculation anomaly\r\nC. Update anomaly\r\nD. Deletion anomaly\r\nE. Compression anomaly",
