    "id": "ch01-rat-page-4",
    "slug": "rat-page-4",
    "title": "RAT: Reading Test — Page 4",
    "content": "## Apply Questions\r\n\r\n**17. A student finishes a SQL chapter but cannot explain why a query matters for a business decision. Which Chapter 1 habit most directly addresses this problem?**\r\n\r\nA. Work steadily\r\n\r\nB. Use the digital materials\r\n\r\nC. Connect technical tasks to business meaning\r\n\r\nD. Pay attention to structure\r\n\r\n**18. A clinic wants to reduce missed appointments. Using the chapter's data-to-decisions arc, which stage turns reliable appointment records into a missed-appointment rate by weekday?**\r\n\r\nA. Data\r\n\r\nB. Tables\r\n\r\nC. Queries feeding analytics\r\n\r\nD. Relationships\r\n\r\n**19. A new analyst is asked to pull the customers who churned last quarter. Applying Chapter 1's SQL Pattern callout, what should the analyst do first?**\r\n\r\nA. Open Power BI and build a dashboard\r\n\r\nB. Write the business question in plain English before writing the query\r\n\r\nC. Export every table to a spreadsheet\r\n\r\nD. Email the manager for a list of churned customers\r\n\r\n**20. A student understands the Grading Database but freezes when starting the PetVax lab. According to Chapter 1, what is this student being asked to do that goes beyond repeating one example?**\r\n\r\nA. Memorize PetVax field names\r\n\r\nB. Recognize the same relational structure in a new business context\r\n\r\nC. Learn a new query language for PetVax\r\n\r\nD. Switch from SQL to spreadsheets\r\n\r\n**21. A retailer wants to compare two possible database designs and recommend the stronger one. Which Bloom level, as described in Chapter 1, does this task target?**\r\n\r\nA. Remember\r\n\r\nB. Understand\r\n\r\nC. Apply\r\n\r\nD. Evaluate\r\n\r\n**22. Select ALL that apply: In the Chapter 1 Let's Build preview, which finished Grading Database questions would likely require SQL or query logic later in the book?**\r\n\r\nA. What is a student's average quiz score?\r\n\r\nB. Which deliverables are still missing scores?\r\n\r\nC. What is the minimum final grade a student could still earn?\r\n\r\nD. What color should the course homepage use?\r\n\r\nE. What letter grade corresponds to a student's current average?\r\n\r\n**23. Select ALL that apply: A team is choosing tools for a workflow that collects customer feedback, stores it relationally, queries it, and shows results to managers. Based on Chapter 1's tool table, which pairings are sensible?**\r\n\r\nA. Google Forms for collection\r\n\r\nB. Supabase / PostgreSQL for relational storage\r\n\r\nC. Lucidchart for live dashboards\r\n\r\nD. SQL for querying\r\n\r\nE. Power BI for managerial reporting\r\n\r\n**24. A student keeps getting wrong results from a query in Let's Build. Which Chapter 1 success habit best frames the student's next move?**\r\n\r\nA. Treat errors as clues that point to something worth learning\r\n\r\nB. Move on to the next chapter and return later\r\n\r\nC. Replace the query with a spreadsheet pivot table\r\n\r\nD. Avoid running the query until the instructor reviews it",
