    "id": "ch02-rat-page-6",
    "slug": "rat-page-6",
    "title": "RAT: Reading Test — Page 6",
    "content": "## Evaluate Questions\r\n\r\n**33. A company's leadership is deciding whether to invest $2 million in a new enterprise resource planning system. Applying BITM thinking, which question is most important to answer first?**\r\n\r\nA. Which vendor has the most advanced features?\r\n\r\nB. What business goals will this system support, and how will we measure whether it creates value?\r\n\r\nC. How long will installation take?\r\n\r\nD. What color should the dashboard be?\r\n\r\n**34. Select ALL that apply: A university wants to improve student retention. Which of the following approaches best reflects the chapter's data-to-performance logic?**\r\n\r\nA. Buy the most expensive analytics platform available\r\n\r\nB. Define retention as a measurable KPI with a clear formula and data source\r\n\r\nC. Identify the data needed — enrollment, attendance, grades, advising contacts\r\n\r\nD. Design dashboards that surface at-risk students before they disengage\r\n\r\nE. Trust that any system will improve outcomes automatically\r\n\r\n**35. A manager proposes buying a software tool that promises to \"fix all reporting problems.\" Based on the chapter's distinction between IT and IS, what is the best response?**\r\n\r\nA. \"Buy it immediately — new software always solves problems.\"\r\n\r\nB. \"A tool alone is IT, not IS. We also need to define processes, train people, set data standards, and connect reports to decisions.\"\r\n\r\nC. \"Software tools are never useful for reporting.\"\r\n\r\nD. \"Only the IT department should make this decision.\"\r\n\r\n**36. In the chapter's terms, which KPI design is stronger for a customer service team?**\r\n\r\nA. \"Improve customer satisfaction.\"\r\n\r\nB. \"Reduce average call time to under two minutes.\"\r\n\r\nC. \"Increase the percentage of issues resolved on first contact from 65 percent to 80 percent within six months, measured by post-call survey data reviewed weekly.\"\r\n\r\nD. \"Make customers happier.\"\r\n\r\n**37. Select ALL that apply: The chapter argues that artificial intelligence tools still depend on the same foundations this chapter introduced. Which foundations must be in place for AI to add value rather than scale weaknesses?**\r\n\r\nA. Clean, trustworthy data\r\n\r\nB. Clear business processes\r\n\r\nC. Sensible KPIs\r\n\r\nD. Governance over who can act on outputs\r\n\r\nE. The newest GPU hardware\r\n\r\n**38. A delivery company's operations manager notices that on-time delivery has dropped from 94 percent to 87 percent. Applying the five-part IS operating loop, what should happen after the manager sees this output?**\r\n\r\nA. Input — capture more delivery data\r\n\r\nB. Processing — recalculate the delivery times\r\n\r\nC. Feedback — investigate the cause and adjust inputs, processes, or staffing\r\n\r\nD. Storage — archive the delivery records\r\n\r\n**39. An online retailer competes on fast, reliable delivery. Its order-management system was designed for cost minimization — it batches orders for efficiency but adds 36 hours to delivery time. According to the chapter's strategic alignment principle, what is the problem?**\r\n\r\nA. The system is too expensive\r\n\r\nB. The system is not aligned with the company's strategy of fast, reliable delivery\r\n\r\nC. All order-management systems should minimize cost\r\n\r\nD. The retailer should change its strategy to match the system\r\n\r\n**40. Select ALL that apply: A large hospital network is designing a governance structure for its information systems. Based on the chapter's discussion of IT governance, which elements should the governance structure include?**\r\n\r\nA. Clear decision rights — who can approve major system changes\r\n\r\nB. Data ownership assignments — who is responsible for data quality\r\n\r\nC. Risk management processes — how security and compliance risks are handled\r\n\r\nD. Value review mechanisms — how the organization knows whether systems create value\r\n\r\nE. A requirement that every department buy its own software independently",
